{ 10.e4  Ba6  is also fine and here Black has a pleasant choice between @@StartFEN@@1rbq1rk1/p1p2ppp/1pnppn2/8/2PP4/2PQ2P1/P2NPPBP/R1B2RK1 b - - 1 10@@EndFEN@@  10...Na5  11.Nb3  and now  11...Ba6!  , allowing  12.Nxa5  bxa5  ,  but the c4-pawn remains weak, or to play }
