11. Nb3
{ We have reached a tricky position because White is threatening Bg5; if we want to keep our pawn structure safe, the retreat ... Ne8 would run into Bxc6 and Be7.   Unfortunately, we cannot play the prophylactic  11...h6  because of  12.Bxh6!  when Qf3 next attacks both knights.  @@StartFEN@@1rb2rk1/p1pq1ppp/1pnppn2/8/2PP4/1NPQ2P1/P3PPBP/R1B2RK1 b - - 3 11@@EndFEN@@  11...Ba6  12.Bg5  d5  leads to a very interesting, objectively equal position, but it is also very tricky, therefore I suggest instead a very deep move here. }
