{ And once again we see the idea of ...Nf4 and ...N6h5. } 20. Qe3 N6h5
{ With a great position as ...Qg5 is coming next. We see in all these lines that the knight has an excellent position on e6 and this explains why taking on a6 in this variation is ill-advised for White. }
