1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. f3
{ This is quite a popular line, played from time to time by many top players. For example, Mamedyarov has enjoyed many nice games with it. }
4... d5
{ We will choose the variation with  4...d5  .  Maybe it is not the most popular solution, but I think it is an interesting option to avoid the main-line theory. }
