{ Now it is time to ask the bishop which diagonal it is going to choose. } 8.
Bh4 Re8
{ A very annoying move from White's point of view as White suddenly has to deal with many tactical threats. Black is even threatening @@StartFEN@@rnbqr1k1/pp3pp1/3ppn1p/2pP4/1bP1P2B/2N2P2/PP4PP/R2QKBNR b KQ - 2 9@@EndFEN@@  9......exd5  10.cxd5  and  10...Nxe4  with the idea of ...Bxd8 Nxc3+ winning back the queen with a big material advantage. It is not so easy to hold the center now. }
9. Ne2
{ White closes the action on the e-file, but at the same time, the f1-bishop has failed to develop. }
9... exd5 10. cxd5 Nbd7 11. Qc2 Ne5
{ A very standard maneuver in this structure. Black activates the d7-knight and intends to unpin with ...Ng6 next. }
12. a3 Ba5 { Of course, we do not resign our nice bishop to an early fate. }
13. Nc1 Ng6
{ And White was forced to give up the important bishop, otherwise the d5-pawn falls. }
14. Bxf6 Qxf6
{ With a dream position for Black in the game Mamedyarov-Korobov, Huaian 2017. }
