13. Bh4 { It is best to remove the bishop from the tactical ideas. } 13... Nxc3
14. Bxh7+
{ White is winning back one pawn, but this is not even enough for equality. }
14... Kxh7 15. Qc2+ Kg8 16. Nxc3 Ne5
{ The knight finds an excellent outpost on d3. White's problem is that even after winning the d6-pawn. }
17. Be7
{ 17.e4  Re8  was just a pawn up for Black in the game Xiong-Grover, Dallas 2015. }
17... Re8 18. Bxd6
{ White has finally won back the pawns, but Black has complete domination. }
18... Nd3
{ The d3-knight is a huge piece! Having opposite color bishops only favours Black because of the extra attacking chances, and the pawn structure is visibly very dangerous for White. All in all, Black stands much better. }
