11. Bb3 Bb7
{ I already prefer Black as it looks like a perfect isoliani structure with an ideal arrangement of the pieces. }
12. Rc1 Nbd7 13. d5
{ White tries this thematic break, having in mind the idea of  13...Bxc3  14.dxe6  . }
13... Nc5 { Black responds instead with this knight move. } 14. dxe6 fxe6
{ The engine prefers this move and gives a nice advantage for Black because of the very well-placed pieces and soon-to-be-obtained two bishops, but if somebody is worried about the pawn structure, then of course  14...Nxe6  gives equality. }
