6. Nf3 Ne4
{ There are other good moves as well, but it looks tempting to either crush the pawn structure or grab the bishop pair. }
7. Bd2
{ White is better to not allow the capture on c3 as he won't have any compensation for the weaknesses. }
7... Nxd2 8. Nxd2 Bxc5
{ Black has a healthy pawn structure and the bishop pair. The only question is if it is realistic to play for an advantage or not. }
9. e3 { Black can start to play actively with ...f5. } 9... f5 10. Be2 O-O 11.
O-O b6
