10... c6 11. Bd3 Nfd7
{ A very interesting idea, trying to make use of the extra ...c6 move. White has the chance to force a draw now with  12.Bxh7+  Kxh7  13.Qh5  and deliver a perpetual check on the squares h5 and f7, but having the white pieces, no one should aim to force a draw in just 12 moves! Such a finish counts as a moral and theoretical victory for Black. }
12. f4 Qh4+ 13. g3 Qh3
{ Black successfully creates a lot of holes on the light squares in White's camp and the upcoming play is an attempt to cash in on this new factor. }
