{ As I said earlier @@StartBracket@@and it is always worth repeating, hence your choice of Chessable!@@EndBracket@@, I consider this type of position to be strategically perfectly fine for Black. }
10. Bd3 Re8 11. O-O Bc7
{ I prefer to improve our bishop first, before transferring the knight to g6, because like this we keep our important ...c6-c5 resource alive against White's f3-idea. }
12. Qc2
{ 12.f3  c5!=  It is very important to remember to have the ... c5-thrust ready for when White plays the f3-move. We are trying to avoid White continuing with e4 next. }
12... Nf8
{ 12...h5!?  is also possible, again keeping the option of playing ...c5 against White's f3. }
13. Rac1 Ng4
{ Is an important tactical option in such positions. The idea will be made clear in just two moves. }
14. h3 Nxe3 { A small but beautiful tactic, which appeared out of nowhere! }
15. Bxe3 Bxg3 16. fxg3 Rxe3 { And Black is a clear pawn up. } *

