{ And the black pieces very quickly join the game. } 13. Be2 Nbd5
{ White's b4-pawn is under attack. } 14. Rb1 axb4 15. axb4 Nxc3
{ A few pieces are exchanged, which is usually not a bad idea when you have some space difficulties or deficit. The basic rule is: 'More space, Keep pieces, Less space, Exchange pieces'. }
16. Bxc3 Nd5 17. Bd2 f5
{ The light squares are weak and we are ready to play ...Bd6, ...Qe7 and ...Bd7. This looks like an excellent position for Black. }
