{ Black has sacrificed a pawn but has more than enough compensation with his attacking pieces and the two bishops. In particular, thanks to the last move  19...Rg4  ,  White is forced to make a weakening move in front of his king. In addition, almost all of White's pieces are misplaced, which gives Black more than sufficient compensation for the pawn minus. }
