11. Nf4
{ 11.Bb5  makes no sense; Black is happy to exchange the bishops with  11...Bd7  . }
11... Ba6
{ Black had other interesting options as well, but - in general - exchanging the bishops is logical if we can successfully protect our center afterward. }
12. Qf3 Bxd3
{ Black usually enjoys an excellent position after the light bishops are exchanged. }
13. Nxd3 Nc6 { And again we manage to get our knight to c6 instead of d7! } 14.
dxc5 bxc5 15. Rfd1
{ I think if we take a 'fresh look' from above at the current position, it is easy to see that only Black is trying to be better here. }
15... c4 16. Nf4 Ne5 17. Qh3 Rb8
{ Black has pressure on the b-file, the queen on h3 is not great, and the same goes for the bishop on d2. Black is pushing, as seen in Nakamura-Gelfand, Monaco 2011. }
