12. Be3 c4
{ This move seems to be good now, as we are a lot of tempos up, so White's counterplay on the kingside will arrive too slow. }
13. Bc2 Nc6 { The knight as usual takes up a nice position on c6. } 14. f5 h6
{ Preventing Bg5 and next Black will continue his play on the queenside, with the main idea of playing ...b5. }
