15... Qd7 { Protecting the d5-pawn. } 16. Re1 Bxd3 17. Nxd5
{ 17.Qxd3  Nc6  is just better for Black. } 17... Nc6
{ We have to stay sharp. } 18. Ne7+ { Tactics everywhere! } 18... Nxe7 19.
Qxa8+ Nc8
{ And once again we find ourselves in a 2 pieces vs rook+pawn position, which should give equal chances. }
