{ We are faced with an interesting position: White has the bishop pair which is clearly a plus and theoretically - if White manages to develop comfortably - a small, long-term advantage. On the other hand, White lost a tempo on playing a3 and now Black has some development advantage.   The question is: does Black have enough time to create some play, or will White will be able to fulfill the dreams of a small but long-term bishop pair advantage. In my opinion, Black has enough resources to be doing fine. }
