12. Rac1 Qb7 13. Rfd1 c5
{ If White can not attack something fast @@StartBracket@@and this is usually Black's d5-pawn@@EndBracket@@ the position is almost certainly OK. }
14. dxc5 bxc5
{ Black will comfortably hold and support his center. The only question might be Qb5. }
15. Qb5 Qb6
{ Black accepts the queen exchange, but only with an improvement of the pawn structure. We are heading towards an equal endgame. }
