12. Ne2
{ This is a popular move nowadays and also a very dangerous one, which we have to take very seriously. Even Carlsen got into a worse position against it @@StartBracket@@he played  12...Qc8  @@EndBracket@@, therefore I will suggest an improvement. }
12... c5 13. dxc5 bxc5 14. Bc3
{ This is the whole point of White's play. White would like to play Nf4 and attack the d5-pawn before Black can consolidate and here, instead of the previously played  14...Nc7  of Nisipeanu-Abasov, Austria 2020, Black can try ...Ne4. }
