{ 15.Qa4  Nc7  holds Black's position together. } 15... Nxc3 16. Rxc3 Nc7 17.
Rd3 Qf6
{ Black would like to exchange his d5-weakness for the pawn on b2, and at the same time he is intending to push ...d4! }
18. Qd2 Rab8 19. b3 c4
{ Forcing equality. We must be always very careful here with Black because of the pressure on the d5-pawn. }
20. bxc4 dxc4 21. Rd4 Red8
{ Exchanging the rooks and it is not simple for White to win the c4-pawn. We will get some activity on the b-file, so the position should be around equal. }
