{ We again transpose to a common structure of the 4. e3 Nimzo-Indian, but the queen on c2 is completely misplaced. White not only made a useless move, but the queen also blocks its bishop's route, since the natural Bd3 development can be answered by ...c4! And without White being able to hold the b1-h7 diagonal, Black will occupy it with his own bishop already enjoying a slight advantage. }
