{ We develop the knight and at the same time create the threat of ...Qa5, which could be dangerous for White. }
9. cxd5
{ This is the only line where White tries to preserve the extra pawn, however, nowadays, it is considered to be a bit risky, because it opens the game and Black can get a very strong compensation by using the e-file and playing the bishop on f5 or g4. }
9... exd5
{ White has two wild options here. Both of them were very popular some years ago even at the highest level. We are going to see some really crazy lines. }
10. Nf3 Qf6
