13... O-O 14. Nf3 Rd8 15. Qc3 Bd7 16. b4 Qb6 17. O-O Rac8 18. Qb3 Be8 19. Rc3
{ And here in the game Jankovic-Hracek, Dresden 2007, Black found a smart solution to force some simplifications. }
19... a5 { Attacking White's queenside. } 20. b5 a4
{ An important intermediate move to free the a5-square for the knight. } 21.
Qxa4 Na5 22. Nd4 e5 { We chase the knight out of a very good position on d4. }
23. Nf5 Rxc4 24. Rxc4 Nxc4 25. Qxc4 g6
{ And Black not only regains the b5 pawn, but also the white knight may be misplaced. }
