{ The Bd2 can't escape. } 11... Nxd2 12. Nxd2
{ Here the two main moves are  12...dxc4  and  12...d4  .  12...O-O  also has some following, but I would like to suggest a fourth move, which has been tried in only 3 games so far. The greatest expert on this line is Karjakin, who has demonstrated in many games how to hold a slightly worse endgame in the case of  12...dxc4  . }
