{ 15.c5  is clearly too optimistic, Black could grab the initiative with  15...a5!  because White is behind in development. }
15... Na5
{ Usually, in case the move ...Na5 works, it is obvious that we should play it. Now we need to remember some small tactics. }
16. cxd5 exd5 17. Qb4 { This is White's usual idea. } 17... Qf6
{ Attacking the rook on a1. } 18. Rd1 b6 19. Be2
{ We follow the Dreev-Rozum game, Cheboksary 2021, where we could make a slight improvement. }
19... Rfc8
{ Followed by ...Rc5 on the next move with a perfectly correct and playable position.Conclusion: in my opinion 4. Qc2 followed by 5. a3 is one of the most dangerous lines White can play against the Nimzo. We must remember well at least the first moves: a small mistake in the move order could lead to an unknown or worse position. The good news is that the line is well analyzed and has been played at the top level for many years, so expecting someone to come along with a 'huge and overwhelming' novelty is very unlikely. I think the right 'slogan' for the current line should be: hard work over talent! }
