1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. Qc2 d5 5. cxd5 exd5 6. Bf4
{ Recently very popular even at higher levels and a very sharp alternative to the main line  6.Bg5  . }
6... c5 { The most challenging move with a quick attack on the center. } 7. Nf3
Nc6 8. a3
{ White tries to strengthen the center.  8.dxc5  O-O  would transpose to the main line. }
8... Bxc3+ 9. bxc3
{ In general, as we already know, we do not have to fear these structures, having White the queen that is not perfectly positioned. }
9... Qa5 { Black is ready to take on d4 to obtain a better pawn structure. }
10. dxc5 Bf5
{ A tactical move that allows the bishop to achieve a good position. } 11. Qb3
{ 11.Qb2  would have been the best chance, but Black is doing fine anyway after  11...Ne4  12.e3  Nxc5 }
11... Ne4 12. Be3 { If  12.e3  then  12...Nxc3  would cause real problems. }
12... O-O
{ And the position could be already evaluated as clearly better for Black. }
13. Rc1 Rfd8 14. Nd4
{ The following moves are just an example of what might happen next. } 14...
Nxc5 15. Qb2 Nxd4 16. Bxd4 Ne6
{ With strong initiative as White is still far away from completing the development. Sahidi-Harikrishna, Czech League 2021. }
