1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. Qc2 d5 5. cxd5 exd5 6. Bg5
{ Probably the main move of our 4. Qc2 Nimzo-Indian. } 6... h6
{ It is very important not to forget to play instantly  6...h6  . } 7. Bxf6
{ There is nothing to worry about once you see the bishop taking on f6. } 7...
Qxf6 8. a3
{ The idea of this line for White is that the bishop 'must' take on c3 now, otherwise the d5-pawn is lost. }
8... Bxc3+ 9. Qxc3
{ It leads to much quieter positions. White would like to achieve a typical Carlsbad structure @@StartBracket@@once Black plays ...c6@@EndBracket@@, where he wants to fight for a small initiative with the standard minority attack with b4-b5 in the long run. However, Black has a more dynamic way of handling the position. }
9... O-O 10. e3 Bf5
{ Black is ready to sacrifice the c-pawn, since it would be suicidal to capture that pawn without finishing the development. Black would invade with the rooks the c-file. Otherwise, Black would want to spare the move ...c6 and play instead for ...Nd7 and the quick ...c5. }
11. Ne2 { With the idea to get the knight to g3. } 11... Nd7 12. Ng3 c5
{ Is still strong. Black does not need worry about losing the bishop, he focuses on a quick initiative until White has not finished the development.  13.dxc5  would be met by  13...Qxc3  14.bxc3  and  14...Be6  followed by taking on c5. Sometimes Black can already get an edge as the c3- and a3-pawns are weaker than the one on d5.   If White plays  13.Bb5  , Black can play for an advantage with  13...c4!  ,  as the bishop on b5 might get trapped after we play ...Nb6. }
13. Nxf5 Qxf5 14. dxc5 d4
{ This great sacrifice is the central point! White opens the files as long as the king is still on e1. 15. exd4 Rfe8+ would be very dangerous for White, as he would not be able to castle, while playing 15.exd4 Nxc5 is more than sufficient compensation. }
15. Bd3 { White's strongest reply. } 15... dxc3 16. Bxf5 cxb2 17. Rb1 Nxc5 18.
Rxb2 g6 19. Bc2 Rfd8
{ Followed by ...Rac8 with an equal endgame happened in the game Atalik-Parligras, Serbian League 2016. }
