[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "20) Nimzo Indian with 4.Qc2, 5.cxd5 and 6.Bg5"]
[Black "6.Bg5 h6 7.Bh4 with 10.f3 #1"]
[Result "*"]

1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. Qc2 d5 5. cxd5 exd5 6. Bg5
{ Probably the main move of our 4. Qc2 Nimzo-Indian. } 6... h6
{ It is very important not to forget to play instantly  6...h6  . } 7. Bh4 g5
{ The main theoretical lines begin with  7...c5  8.dxc5  g5  9.Bg3  Ne4  with thousands of games and extreme complications. I would like to suggest a rare alternative, which is gaining popularity today after several top GMs have used it successfully. }
8. Bg3 Nc6
{ We do not usually put the knight on c6 before playing the move c5, but in this line there is a concrete reason to do so. }
9. e3 h5
{ A very dynamic variation, where it is easy to play for a win from the opening stage of the game. We got right to the crossroads, White tried 7 different moves here. }
10. f3 Qe7
{ Black attacks the e3- and also the d4-pawn. The move ...Qe7 in general should be kept in the memory: it also support the idea of ...O-O-O at some point. }
11. Qd2
{ This move was played in several games, but Black can build up a big advantage with a nice strategical plan. }
11... h4 12. Bf2 g4
{ There is no time to waste! Black has the better development and is making use out of it. }
13. O-O-O h3
{ A very nice way to solve the light squares problem. Black simply wants to take on g2 and then on f3, followed by ...Bf5 and the occupation of the e4-square. }
14. Qc2
{ 14.a3  hxg2  15.Bxg2  gxf3  16.Bxf3  Bxc3  17.Qxc3  and here Grandelius should have played  17...Bf5  with a big advantage. }
14... hxg2 15. Bxg2
{ Now we take the knight out of the game to have even more control over the e4-square. }
15... Bxc3 16. bxc3 gxf3 17. Bxf3 Bg4
{ And even if the position looks strange, it is clear that Black has an excellent play. }
18. Kb2 O-O-O
{ With the great triumph of the light squares strategy. Black will occupy the squares e4 and c4 with knights and could also use the typical ...Rh6 idea to move the attack on the queenside. Hoyer-Hammer, Helsingor 2016 }
*

