{ A very dynamic variation, where it is easy to play for a win from the opening stage of the game. We got right to the crossroads, White tried 7 different moves here. }
10. Bd3 Qe7
{ This seems to be the stronger reaction with two ideas in mind: Black has just created the threat of ...Nxd4 and furthermore the move h4 now traps the bishop. }
11. Nf3 { Black should accept the provocation and proceed aggressively. } 11...
h4 12. Be5 g4 13. Nd2
{ White is using the fact that taking twice on e5 runs into Qa4 check. The d5-pawn is suddenly under attack, but Black can use the rook again to join the battle. }
13... Rh5 { Now the e5-bishop is really in trouble. } 14. Bxf6 Qxf6 15. O-O-O
{ On  15.a3  , I suggest the same reaction with  15...Bxc3  16.Qxc3  Bf5  ,  followed by O-O-O with a comfortable game. }
15... Bxc3
{ Black had many other options as well, but this improvement on the game Rios-Garriga Cazorla, Barbera del Valles 2021, seems to be the easiest way to get a nice position. }
16. Qxc3 Bf5
{ Followed by O-O-O. Objectively the position is still equal, but it is easier to play with Black. }
