{ Using the idea that White is not yet prepared to push  8.d5?  in view of a quick  8...exd5  followed by ...Re8, after which the center collapses on White. }
8. Bg2 Bb7 9. e5 Ne8
{ Black's pieces look passive, but White's center is in a precarious situation. }
10. O-O
{ While White finishes his development, Black is prepared to undermine the center with ...d6. }
10... d6 11. Qe2 Nd7
{ And a kind of clearing of the position with mass exchanges is inevitable, after which a drawish position will arise. }
12. Rad1 cxd4 { It is time to start the exchanges. } 13. exd6 Nxd6 14. Nxd4
{ White cannot avoid the exchange of the Bb7 vs Bg2. } 14... Bxg2 15. Kxg2 Qc7
{ With equality. } *

