{ A solid move that often leads to structures known from the Queen's Indian Defense 4.e3 line, with a big difference - the knight is standing on d2 instead of the more active c3-square. Therefore, Black can choose to preserve his bishop. }
5... O-O 6. Bd3
{ 6.a3  Be7  should not make any difference, as White needs to complete development with Bd3 and O-O. }
6... d5
{ The most concrete way to fight for the center with the idea of following up with ...Bb7, ...Nbd7 and ...c5. }
7. O-O Bb7 8. a3 Be7 { Of course, we do not give away the bishop pair. } 9. Qc2
{ The idea of pushing e4 is typical, but not good at this precise moment. Black is perfectly prepared for it. }
