{ This line has been played by Khalifman, trying to improve some future capture on c5, and using the idea that he might still get a better structure if Black plays ...c4 or ...cxb4. However, Black can also improve his position, starting with ...Rc8. }
13... Rc8 14. Bf5
{ And now in the game Khalifman-Hertneck, Germany 1996, Black should have just left the pin with ...Rc7. }
14... Rc7
{ Also protecting the b7-bishop in some cases, with a fine position. } *

